Why Organics?

Clean Food, Grown with Care

We farm the way nature intended — without synthetic pesticides, GMOs, or harmful chemicals. By nourishing our soil and rotating our crops, we grow produce that’s better for you and better for the planet.

Our organic practices mean fresher flavors, healthier meals, and a cleaner conscience.

 Frequently Asked Questions

Everything you need to know about shopping with us.

Where does your produce come from?

All of our fruits, vegetables, and pantry items are grown or made right here on our family farm. When needed, we may partner with trusted nearby farms that follow the same organic and sustainable practices.

Is everything you sell certified organic?

Most entities doing business in organic trade need to be certified: there are very few exceptions to this. Except for exempt operations, any operation that produces or handles organic agricultural products must be certified.

How does the subscription box work?

Customers pay in advance for these boxes, which contain an assortment of products and usually focus on a specific theme or interest.

Where do you deliver?

From beer and wine, to bread and biscuits, dozens of our certified shops and businesses are now offering online delivery of organic food and drink products across the UK.

Is your packaging eco-friendly?

Opt for materials that are recyclable, biodegradable, or made from renewable resources.
